## 13. Security & Production Notes

- **Control DB credentials** for provisioning have `CREATE`, `DROP`, `GRANT` and are isolated from runtime read-only credentials.
- **Passwords** are encrypted at rest (via `EncryptionService`) and never logged.
- **Tenant DB users** receive least privilege (`SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, ALTER, INDEX, DROP` on their DB only).
- **No shell execution** — all installation uses WordPress APIs loaded from the shared Bedrock core.
- **Amazon RDS** compatible: uses `IF NOT EXISTS` syntax, avoids `SUPER`, uses `%` host wildcard.

